The Grubby Chest can be found on the south-west corner of the Forthos Dungeon, behind a locked gate that requires level 57 Thieving to open. The chest is locked and can only be opened by using a grubby key, which is obtained from killing monsters in the Forthos Dungeon. There is a warning message when attempting to open the chest with fewer than 11 free inventory spaces, which can be disabled.

Rewards[edit | edit source]

Drop rates estimated based on 72,344 chests from the Drop Rate Project, unless otherwise cited.

The average Grubby Chest open is worth 50,280.76.

The Grubby Chest uses a special mechanic to determine the items obtained from the chest.

30 June 2021

13 January 2021
(update)

The Grubby Chest now has a 'Check' option which tells how many times it has been opened by the player.

11 July 2019
(update)

The Grubby Chest will now give Red dragonhide and Dragon bones in noted form.
